  <mainDescription>&lt;h4>&#xD;
    Case study&#xD;
&lt;/h4>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The studies will consist of high level descriptions of the cases, with descriptions of the main processes that the&#xD;
    cases involve, and detailed use cases describing both the current “as-is” situations as well as possible&#xD;
    “to-be”-situations where it is shown how Future Internet technologies can be used to improve the processes. Selected&#xD;
    use cases will be refined further, generating specifications for experimentation in the cases as well as methods for&#xD;
    evaluating the results from the experimentation. These will again be used for generating large-scale trial plans for&#xD;
    the second phase of the FI-PPP programme. Figure 1 describes the main components of the studies to be carried out and&#xD;
    their relations to Future Internet and Experimentation Environment.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;./resources/fig1.png&quot; width=&quot;600&quot; height=&quot;485&quot; />&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h4>&#xD;
    Recommended workflow&#xD;
&lt;/h4>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
        href=&quot;./../../../practice.requirements.case_study.base-sintef/capabilitypatterns/case_study_definition_6D7E805F.html&quot;&#xD;
         guid=&quot;_0f-2oaJDEeC2rPq2LOW9Ag&quot;>Case study definition&lt;/a>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The first task&amp;nbsp;is to define a worfklow&amp;nbsp;and tasks for&amp;nbsp;gathering data for the use cases, giving guidelines&#xD;
    both for how to gather data and what kind of data is expected from the use cases. Guidelines for the following will be&#xD;
    provided:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;div align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
            what data should be collected&#xD;
        &lt;/div>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;div align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
            suggestions on how data can be collected&#xD;
        &lt;/div>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;div align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
            a structure for presenting and organizing the use cases which is an important base for the work on the case&#xD;
            studies across all tasks in the Finest project.&#xD;
        &lt;/div>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;h4 align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
    Relations between tasks and work packages&#xD;
&lt;/h4>&#xD;
&lt;p align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
    Inputs from other tasks that run in parallel are required in order to develop a valid and solid methodology.&amp;nbsp;To&#xD;
    ensure synchronization and cooperation among the different related tasks the same people are assigned to these&#xD;
    activities. The output from this task is intended for use with the case study scenario descriptions, but it is also&#xD;
    important to create a structure and methodology that ties the case studies to the rest of the work in the project.&#xD;
    Figure 2 below shows the relationships between the methodology task (T2.1) and the other tasks in the project.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
    &lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;./resources/fig2.png&quot; width=&quot;600&quot; height=&quot;447&quot; />&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
